columns.name: Id
columns.description: ID number associated with pole

columns.name: Reservation Date
columns.description: The date that pole was reserved by franchisee

columns.name: Franchisee Name
columns.description: Franchisee name e.g. Mobilitie, Crown Castle, etc.

columns.name: Status
columns.description: Status of pole reservation e.g. “Proposed” (franchisee has submitted an application but has not yet received City approval), “Approved” (pole reservation has been approved by the City), “Installed” (franchisee has completed construction).

columns.name: Installation Date
columns.description: The date that the equipment installation was completed

columns.name: Pole Class
columns.description: City-owned light pole or privately-owned wooden utility pole

columns.name: Borough
columns.description: Borough - Manhattan, Bronx, Brooklyn, Queens, and Staten Island

columns.name: X Coord.
columns.description: The x coordinate is a given number of pixels along the horizontal axis based on the World Geodetic System (WGS1984) standard. This Property Level Information x coordinate is approximated to the location based on the address range.

columns.name: Y Coord.
columns.description: The y coordinate is a given number of pixels along the vertical axis based on the World Geodetic System (WGS1984) standard. This Property Level Information y coordinate is approximated to the location based on the address range.

columns.name: Latitude
columns.description: Points that fall North or South of the Equator, expressed in degrees.

columns.name: Longitude
columns.description: Points that fall East or West of the Prime Meridian, expressed in degrees.

columns.name: Zone
columns.description: A, B, and C ("Zone A” means the portion of the Borough of Manhattan which includes 96th Street (inclusive of the northernmost boundary of the north side sidewalk of 96th Street) and all parts of said Borough that lie south of 96th Street. “Zone B” means all portions of the City not within Zone A or Zone C. “Zone C” means Community Districts 1, 2, 4, 5, and 7 in the Borough of the Bronx and Community Districts 13 and 16 in the Borough of Brooklyn.”)
